1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 6-09 of the North Dakota Century
2 Code, relating to a housing development loan fund; to provide an appropriation; to provide a
3 continuing appropriation; to provide for a transfer; to provide an expiration date; and to declare
4 an emergency.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 6-09 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
7 and enacted as follows:
8 Housing development loan fund - Continuing appropriation - Audit and costs of
9 administration - Transfer to general fund.
10 1. The housing development loan fund is a special fund in the state treasury. The Bank of
11 North Dakota shall administer the fund for the purpose of providing loans to banks in
12 the state to establish housing development loan programs to assist housing builders
13 and developers in the county in which the local bank is located.
14 2. Loans provided under this section:
15 a. May not exceed five million dollars in total to local banks in each county except
16 that loans to banks located in counties that receive more than five million dollars
17 of oil and gas gross production tax revenue allocations per year may not exceed
18 ten million dollars in total ;
19 b. Must have an interest rate equal to two percent; and
20 c. Must provide for repayment by June 30, 2030.
21 3. The Bank shall deposit in the housing development loan fund all payments of principal
22 and interest paid under a loan made from the housing development loan fund. The
23 Bank may use a portion of the interest paid on the outstanding loans as a servicing fee
24 to pay for administrative costs, including the cost of an audit of the fund in accordance
